dsmr-email-admin (1.0-10) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Add a 'rotate' subcommand to rotate the vpopmail PostgreSQL role password
    in one verified step: generate a new password, ALTER ROLE, rewrite
    vpopmail.pgsql (with a timestamped backup), regenerate the dovecot SQL
    conf, and reload dovecot.  The password is never printed.  Supports
    --dry-run.  Removes the need to hand-edit credentials when rotating a
    suspected-exposed or aged backend password.

