dsmr-email-admin (1.0-5) trixie; urgency=low

  * Add a 'reputation' subcommand for outbound-IP reputation problems:
      - 'reputation audit': detect backscatter (null-sender bounces in the
        queue), list the accept-then-bounce recipients and classify each as a
        real user with broken delivery or a non-existent account, flag a
        ~alias/.qmail-default fastforward catch-all that bounces unknowns, and
        count mailbox forwards to external freemail;
      - 'reputation probe LOCAL@DOMAIN': test the RCPT gate as a real external
        sender via this host's own public IP (127.0.0.1 is a relayclient and
        would mask the answer);
      - 'reputation purge [--commit]': remove null-sender "failure notice"
        backscatter from the queue, leaving real mail untouched.

 -- Brian O'Reilly <fade@deepsky.com>  Thu, 04 Jun 2026 21:00:00 -0400

